description: With power on, keep the black probe on the control‑module 0 V node (the internal node where the Control Input Cable (−) connects). Measure DC voltage at (1) the internal node where Control Input Cable (+) lands, (2) the node on the switch ‘through’ line feeding the control output (+), and (3) the anode and cathode of the inverted‑cables indicator LED. Record polarity and magnitude at each point relative to the control 0 V node. This is to confirm whether the control cube internally inverts the labeling of its (+) and (−) input terminals or routes them incorrectly to the LED/switch line., outcome='Measured at the internal node where Control Input Cable (+) lands: approximately −11.99 V relative to the control 0 V node.  \nMeasured at the switch “through” line feeding the control output (+): approximately −11.99 V relative to the control 0 V node (no differential between p and n).  \nMeasured at the inverted‑cables indicator LED: anode at approximately −0.00 V and cathode at approximately −1.29 V relative to the control 0 V node.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
